Rules of Professional Conduct, pertaining to fee- splitting.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>WTP applied for supervisory writs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The court of appeal granted writs and
remanded the case to the trial court to allow WTP to amend their petition to
state a cause of action for unjust enrichment.<i>“We the People” Paralegal
Services, LLC v. Watley, </i>33,480<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>(La. App. 2d Cir. 8/25/00), 766 So. 2d 744.<span style='font-size:11.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div style='mso-element:endnote' id="edn4">

<p class="MsoNormal" style='margin-bottom:12.0pt;text-align:justify'><a style='mso-endnote-id:edn4' href="#_ednref4" name="_edn4" title=""><span style='font-size:11.0pt'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">     </span></span></a><span class="MsoEndnoteReference"><span style='font-size:11.0pt'>3</span></span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Respondents failed to advise the ODC or the
